nodes.bodyText:
Hi everyone,
EditorContextProvider.getChannel()  will return an Enum with

DEFAULT (on any web app running based on AppFormer);
On Kogito we will return VSCODE|GITHUB|Online based on the channel that the envelope is running;

Our webapps to ensure the correct values are returned in -testing and -runtime will have to implement an
@Alternative for EditorContextProvider that will return the desired channel mock.
I also agree with Michael that is a good idea to remove isKogito() API after this PR gets merged.
Thanks everyone for the discussion. I hope that makes sense and provide value for us.

